eplyTime":"2020-01-08T04:12:55.000Z","msg":"可能好撚多都係永久凍土？"},{"pid":"15824d07e98e56cc3a60761793d36b73873acb2a","tid":1815964,"uid":55055,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2020-01-08T04:13:10.000Z","msg":"我係俄就彩老美都有味<img src=\"/assets/faces/pig/heard.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"d373d8b9dc7ac2d830849cec8efbe4aae4384c1a","tid":1815964,"uid":205043,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2020-01-08T04:14:28.000Z","msg":"我睇過一本美國介紹書<br />\n話美國現時既核武足以毁滅五個地球<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/angel.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"1c6510aa36d86c24201b37e76694ab95478d1eb2","tid":1815964,"uid":313615,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"quote":{"pid":"6d06b0820da6806a4b2c37c1bbb533a70a7c3593","tid":1815964,"uid":231102,"like":3,"dislike":0,"score":3,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2020-01-08T02:26:00.000Z","msg":"以前美國一向抗俄優先過抗支，而家調返轉啦，感謝党<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/adore.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-01-08T04:15:53.000Z","msg":"川普通俄通烏<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/wink.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"a14c570da5af04ea5f3d214a0f5f4bd1caec918b","tid":1815964,"uid":236075,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"quote":{"pid":"d42924168501df60e22997313988e6851b590f71","tid":1815964,"uid":134071,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2020-01-08T02:03:06.000Z","msg":"美國國務卿Mike Pompeo :<br />\n美國與伊朗的衝突, 不會停止美國對抗「中共」. &nbsp;不過, 美國可能尋求跟俄羅斯改善關係<br />\n<br />\n<a href=\"https://www.wsj.com/articles/pompeo-explains-the-iran-policy-11578354990\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Farticles%2Fpompeo-explains-the-iran-policy-11578354990&d=rLp99s1CaA%2FTm5LA4NL6TTvkInyplymEwWc8t9jwBTE%3D&h=e2a00422\" data-auto-link target=\"_blank\">https://www.wsj.com/articles/pompeo-explains-the-iran-policy-11578354990</a><br />\n<br />\nPompeo Explains the Iran Policy<br />\n<strong>And he promises to focus on competition with China and better relations with Russia.</strong><br />\n<br />\nBy Walter Russell Mead<br />\nJan. 6, 2020 6:56 pm ET <br />\n.....<br />\n<strong>This discrepancy emerged in a wide-ranging interview I had last month with Secretary of State Mike Pompeo.</strong><br />\n<br />\nWith respect to Iran, the administration is confident that the combination of America&rsquo;s fracking revolution (which allows the U.S. to exclude Iranian oil from world markets without risking a devastating rise in prices), the dramatic, info-tech enabled increase in the effectiveness of American sanctions, and continuing U.S. military superiority has given America the advantage.<br />\n<br />\nIran, the administration believes, is in a box. The policy of extreme economic pressure through sanctions continues to weaken Iran&rsquo;s economy&mdash;and the noose will tighten further when new sanctions take effect in 2020. The International Monetary Fund estimates that Iran&rsquo;s GDP contracted 9.5% in 2019, and administration officials believe that the damage could be more than twice as severe in 2020.<br />\n<br />\nFrom Washington&rsquo;s perspective, Iran has three choices.<br />\n<br />\n-It can continue to resist while its domestic economy and regional allies suffer under growing resource constraints.<br />\n-It can launch a large-scale attack on Americans&mdash;or initiate a dash for the bomb, which would pose a substantial threat to U.S. security&mdash;triggering a Pearl Harbor-like reaction from the Jacksonian base, which would sustain a massive military response.<br />\n-Or it can enter into serious negotiations over ending its nuclear program, its missile program, and its scheme of terror and subversion in neighboring states.<br />\n<br />\nMeanwhile, <strong>officials believe the confrontation with Iran won&rsquo;t force the administration off course when it comes to the biggest issue of the day: competition with China. Here again, Mr. Pompeo believes the administration is making headway. </strong>The North Atlantic Treaty Organization, he argues, faces serious threats from Chinese cyberattacks, influence operations and efforts &ldquo;to eat away at core democracies around the fringes of the NATO region.&rdquo; Europe is also taking more seriously the surveillance threat from Huawei&rsquo;s 5G equipment.<br />\n<br />\n<strong>Mr. Pompeo also appears to believe that the rise of China creates an opportunity for a different relationship with Russia. &ldquo;We&rsquo;ve talked with the Russians,&rdquo; he says. &ldquo;The Russians want a better relationship with the United States of America.&rdquo;</strong> Of Foreign Minister Sergei Lavrov, he says, &ldquo;I&rsquo;ll probably spend a great deal of time with him . . . as will my colleagues in the cabinet trying to find places where we can work together.&rdquo;<br />\n<br />\nConfrontation with Iran, competition with China, outreach to Russia&mdash;this is both a bold agenda internationally and a deeply controversial one at home. Undaunted by critics, unfazed by opponents, Messrs. Trump and Pompeo seem determined to go on reshaping American foreign policy right up through the November election and beyond. Whether their policies will be crowned with success cannot be predicted, but at the start of 2020 the Trump administration appears to have a clear course in mind."},"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-01-08T04:21:09.000Z","msg":"老美腹背受敵，如果中俄伊朝一齊上<img src=\"/assets/faces/pig/shocked.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"69bb519f26ba77587795d6df89024461fa99ff30","tid":1815964,"uid":134071,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-01-08T04:23:12.000Z","msg":"<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/kill.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/kill.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/kill.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/kill.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"fb013a79b657e3f3afab93bc251471d300db1909","tid":1815964,"uid":236075,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"quote":{"pid":"d373d8b9dc7ac2d830849cec8efb